CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1950, pg. 3, reads: "What Do They Care? - The practice of parking cars on the wrong side of Herron Avenue between Wylie and Bryn Mawr has been going on so long that nobody seems to care any more. Police "No Parking at Anytime" signs don't mean a thing.  Is "politics" keeping the police form enforcing the no-parking regulation? - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Herron Avenue, between Wylie Avenue and Bryn Mawr Road, showing The Bell Shop, Rexall Drugs, Speck's Market, and billboard advertising John Wesley AME Zion Church
